description: Tammy Winger Forchion  added  6 new photos  ‚Äî with  Tyler Rose  and  Olivia Rose  in  Flagstaff, Arizona . One year ago we ( Tyler Rose  and  Olivia Rose ) settled into  Flagstaff Medical Center  for a long evening. We were awaiting for the arrival of Ellie Joan Rose. The two of them worked in tandem together. It was so amazing as they followed their plan. He never left her side. One point in the evening Olivia woke me after about 15 min of sleep. She did not want to wake Tyler. She knew how tired he was. She asked me a few questions. I went out in the hallway for a nurse. When entering the room he was at her side. The next hour he was there with every contraction and moment. He focused her. 12 hours later Ellie entered the world. The two of them quickly became 3. Ellie knew her parents in a way I cannot even describe. She looked at her mom and had a smile as she focused on her mother and soon her father. It was a peaceful beautiful time. They have made it through a year of a a new job for Tyler, the last year of nursing school for Olivia, incorporating the two girls into a family, and now moving forward as Olivia begins her career as a nurse @TubeCity hospital and Tyler starts school. They have faced challenges and great times. Many have joined in her life creating a sense of security, love, adjustment, and connection as the family needed a village to get through the year. Thank you to each person who helped (Ella, Kathee Rose,  Carly Westbrook Winger  Jazz Winger,  Raymond L Forchion Jr.  and many more).   Excited to celebrate the one year party tomorrow of Miss Ellie (named after a great great grandma, 2 great grandmas, and an aunt). She has her own personality and knows exactly what she wants and does not like (socks, cold, and is super focused). HaPpY BiRtHdAy Ellie. Excited to celebrate tomorrow.
